07:54.410 --> 07:56.060
My name is Frank, Frank Whitaker.

07:56.080 --> 07:57.770
If you'll just talk to me.

07:57.800 --> 07:59.130
Not now.

07:59.150 --> 08:00.190
Why not now?

08:00.210 --> 08:03.830
She's probably angry as hell
that I flaked on her, again.

08:04.420 --> 08:07.530
Well, hopefully she'll understand.

08:08.690 --> 08:10.980
- You ok?
- Yeah. Just stretching.

08:10.990 --> 08:13.180
How 'bout some music for the road?

08:14.900 --> 08:18.230
Oh, this song, it was popular when we...

08:18.830 --> 08:21.880
I--sorry--moved
to Grandview.

08:21.900 --> 08:25.790
It was playing when I found the
vacant storefront on town square.

08:27.190 --> 08:30.160
Oh, I get it. You like him.

08:30.170 --> 08:32.679
What, are you married, divorced? What?

08:32.690 --> 08:35.280
Look, I'm not going anywhere, so if
you wanna get me out of your hair--

08:35.289 --> 08:38.630
uh, you know what? I just remembered there's
a phone call that I have to make, so...

08:38.640 --> 08:40.940
Oh, for cryin' out loud.

08:41.909 --> 08:45.460
Hey, Frank. It's Melinda.

08:45.470 --> 08:49.050
Got your voice mail, but it was a
little garbled, so what were you saying?

08:49.060 --> 08:50.080
Thank you.

08:50.100 --> 08:52.910
I rented this truck to haul
some stuff to a coin show.

08:52.930 --> 08:54.700
I'm a numismatist.

08:54.710 --> 08:59.220
Anyway, I was fixing a flat on the shoulder
outside charlotte when the jack gave away.

08:59.230 --> 09:00.490
Man, did that hurt.

09:00.500 --> 09:01.140
Ok, you know what?

09:01.170 --> 09:04.190
The reception's a little rough out here,
so if you could just get to the point.

09:04.210 --> 09:09.630
Ok, there's a 1943 copper penny
fell into a crack at the cargo door.

09:09.650 --> 09:11.500
It's worth a fortune.

09:11.520 --> 09:14.610
I--I been tryin' to pick it up
forever, but, hey, watch this.

09:15.880 --> 09:17.310
My wife could use the money.

09:17.330 --> 09:20.810
I need you to find that
penny and send it to her.

09:20.840 --> 09:24.330
June Whitaker on Allen wood in Raleigh.

09:24.350 --> 09:26.860
She's in the book.
Will you do that for me?

09:26.870 --> 09:29.060
Be happy to help.

09:29.070 --> 09:31.800
Ohh, thank you.

09:32.600 --> 09:35.980
Well, it's about damn time. Ciao.

09:43.190 --> 09:44.760
There weren't enough guys in drama,

09:44.790 --> 09:50.300
So we did some gender bending with
that--that one act by that French guy.

09:50.310 --> 09:51.310
Moliere.

09:51.320 --> 09:52.260
Yes!

09:52.280 --> 09:54.880
Thank god somebody has
a functioning memory.

09:54.920 --> 09:57.940
Anyway, Marla was playing
Valera, the male lover,

09:57.990 --> 10:01.690
And when she kissed
deally, the place went nuts.

10:01.710 --> 10:03.700
Oh, I could imagine.

10:03.740 --> 10:06.280
God, memory lane's
such a dead-end street.

10:06.310 --> 10:07.730
Let's party already.

10:07.760 --> 10:09.650
Eli, I'm so glad you stayed.

10:09.670 --> 10:11.170
Oh, wouldn't have missed it.

10:11.190 --> 10:12.460
Deally, more champagne?

10:12.500 --> 10:14.740
No, no, no. Just 2 is my limit.

10:14.750 --> 10:16.160
You know, motherhood and all.

10:16.180 --> 10:18.070
You never
know when--

10:19.290 --> 10:21.330
that's more like it.

10:21.340 --> 10:26.230
- Deal, d-did you just put
this on? - No. No, I didn't.

10:28.610 --> 10:31.240
Hey, watch it.

10:31.250 --> 10:33.660
This was playing at the wrap party.

10:33.690 --> 10:36.430
Yeah. That was the
night that, uh--

10:37.140 --> 10:39.210
excuse me.

10:40.120 --> 10:44.440
Hello. Yeah.
Hi, Mrs.--

10:45.900 --> 10:48.070
what?

10:52.630 --> 10:53.760
Who are all these people?

10:53.780 --> 10:56.560
Your party must have gone viral.

10:56.570 --> 10:59.310
- This isn't my party.
- Really?

10:59.790 --> 11:02.140
- Then whose is it?
- Mom.

11:03.850 --> 11:05.560
Ok, guys, party's over.

11:05.590 --> 11:07.140
Everybody can start cleaning up!

11:07.150 --> 11:09.800
And nobody is leaving
without a designated driver!

11:09.810 --> 11:12.940
- Mom, listen-- -
no, you listen to me.

11:12.950 --> 11:15.640
You wanna make some excuses,
you can save your breath.

11:15.650 --> 11:17.370
Now, get to work. You're
comin' home with me.

11:17.380 --> 11:19.860
- But this
isn'my-- - now!

11:20.870 --> 11:22.240
Let me just tell you what happened.

11:22.250 --> 11:24.190
No, I know exactly what happened.

11:24.220 --> 11:27.180
You violated my trust and Melinda's.

11:27.190 --> 11:30.260
I told Dylan that I couldn't go out tonight because
I was house-sitting, and then the next thing--

11:30.270 --> 11:32.070
You let them in!

11:32.100 --> 11:34.000
They brought alcohol.

11:34.030 --> 11:35.970
- Were you drinking?
- No.

11:35.980 --> 11:37.830
Will you just chill for a second?

11:37.840 --> 11:41.680
Chill? Come back here,
I'm talking to you.

11:41.690 --> 11:44.420
Please shut up.

11:44.680 --> 11:46.420
Don't be slamming doors!

11:46.440 --> 11:48.900
- I didn't.
- I did.

11:48.910 --> 11:52.060
Stop, ok. Just stop.

11:52.340 --> 11:56.460
You need to go to bed, and I need to
think clearly about your punishment.

11:56.470 --> 11:59.570
Delia Rayburn, the party animal?

11:59.580 --> 12:01.770
No way.

12:08.900 --> 12:11.590
Oh, my god.

12:13.560 --> 12:15.830
How are you?

12:46.720 --> 12:49.090
That was quick. Is that her?

12:49.570 --> 12:52.970
No, her roommate, uh, Cheryl.

12:53.270 --> 12:55.660
Uh, Nicole took off 2 days
after I never showed up,

12:55.670 --> 12:59.940
and then she made Cheryl promise
she'd never tell me where she was.

12:59.950 --> 13:04.350
I'm sorry. So it's a dead end.

13:04.360 --> 13:05.920
Not exactly.

13:05.930 --> 13:08.760
Cheryl gave me Nicoleâs new number.

13:09.920 --> 13:12.850
I didn't wanna do this over the phone.

13:16.790 --> 13:19.210
- hey, it's me. Leave a message.
- Voice mail.

13:19.560 --> 13:21.570
Nicole, hi. It's Sam.

13:21.580 --> 13:28.000
I'm really sorry I never explained to
you why I didn't show up, and I just--

13:28.020 --> 13:30.930
I had this accident, and my
life's been messed up ever since.

13:30.970 --> 13:34.700
Uh, I just would really like a
chance to explain what happened.

13:35.120 --> 13:38.460
Well, I hope to hear from you. Bye.

13:44.290 --> 13:45.570
Hey, you're not
goin' anywhere until--

13:45.580 --> 13:47.280
Melinda's heater guy, remember.

13:47.300 --> 13:49.330
Well, I want you home
right after so we can talk.

13:49.340 --> 13:51.410
Whatever.

14:03.900 --> 14:06.890
Brightness.

14:18.690 --> 14:21.710
When did you get so... Old?

14:27.600 --> 14:31.370
Um, is somebody here?

14:32.730 --> 14:34.030
God.

14:34.040 --> 14:35.770
Come on, doobie-ah.

14:35.800 --> 14:38.310
You know, loosen up a little.

14:38.320 --> 14:40.580
Have some fun.

14:46.280 --> 14:48.730
That'll work.

14:50.270 --> 14:52.090
Ok, where's the ghost?

14:52.120 --> 14:54.650
Uh, this is me you're talking to.

14:54.670 --> 14:56.740
Sorry. I'm not a morning person.

14:56.750 --> 14:58.980
Well, it's in here somewhere.

14:59.000 --> 15:00.730
Well, I believe "it's" a she.

15:00.770 --> 15:02.350
I heard her talking
at dinner last night.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.210
Teenager, kind of snarky.

15:04.230 --> 15:07.420
Well, do you think Ned brought
home some rand ghost girl?

15:07.450 --> 15:11.130
No. I believe she came with your
friends, looking for a party.

15:11.140 --> 15:12.860
Uh, hello?

15:12.890 --> 15:17.420
Whoever you are, I can hear
you, maybe even help you.

15:19.260 --> 15:21.480
Well, if she's here, she's not talkin'.

15:21.490 --> 15:22.770
Oh, my god.

15:22.780 --> 15:25.510
That song that played last night.

15:25.530 --> 15:28.730
Angie Hollenbeck.

15:28.740 --> 15:31.010
She was a girl that we
went to high school with.

15:31.040 --> 15:32.310
I had drama class with her.

15:32.320 --> 15:34.490
She loved to party so...

15:34.510 --> 15:37.090
If it really is Angie, you
gotta help me get rid of her.

15:37.120 --> 15:41.870
That girl was nothing but trouble, just always
wasted, and if she's hangin' around Ned--

15:41.890 --> 15:43.090
How'd she die?

15:43.120 --> 15:48.140
Uh, she got really messed up on
our senior wrap night, and, uh,

15:48.160 --> 15:52.690
She decided to walk home, and then the next
day, we heard that she got hit by a car.

15:53.120 --> 15:57.680
Anyway, that is not the
only reason why I called you.

15:58.310 --> 15:59.990
No, thanks. Makes me paranoid.

16:00.000 --> 16:03.710
No. I-- I found this
here. I know my son.

16:03.720 --> 16:09.660
And this is not like him, and Angie the pothead
just happened to show up at my house the night

16:09.670 --> 16:11.710
Before I find drugs in it.

16:11.720 --> 16:16.030
Oh, sure. Blame me. You suck!

16:18.320 --> 16:21.890
Kids today. Kids yesterday.

16:21.900 --> 16:25.290
This is nuts. You are a therapist.

16:25.300 --> 16:29.450
Ghost or no ghost, how--how am I
supposed to confront Ned about this?

16:29.480 --> 16:33.490
First of all, I wouldn't confront
anyone until I was sure it was his.

16:33.500 --> 16:36.260
What? You had the banger
sisters over here last night.

16:36.530 --> 16:39.780
What makes you think they didn't
bring the ghost and the ganja?

16:45.530 --> 16:47.890
Find something?

16:48.890 --> 16:50.700
See a penny, pick it up.

16:50.710 --> 16:52.810
That's old. That could
be worth something'.

16:52.820 --> 16:58.740
Yeah. I have a--a friend who's a collector,
so whenever I find anything, I send it to her.

16:59.700 --> 17:01.710
You for real?

