Amazing.
Not--not strange.

37:20.000 --> 37:23.050
Would it be wrong of me to want to...

37:24.010 --> 37:26.820
Run into a little traffic here?

37:28.420 --> 37:30.630
Why would you want that?

37:30.660 --> 37:33.320
Make the trip last a little bit longer.

37:38.650 --> 37:42.140
Do you have any idea how
much trouble you're in?

37:42.170 --> 37:44.100
No, but I'm sure you're
gonna tell me all about it.

37:44.110 --> 37:46.290
- Ok, let's all try to-- -
first of all, you're grounded.

37:46.320 --> 37:48.240
Second of all, you're grounded.

37:48.250 --> 37:51.090
Was it really worth it just
risking your life for some party?

37:51.100 --> 37:52.490
That's a little
dramatic, don't you think?

37:52.510 --> 37:53.750
I didn't really risk my life.

37:53.770 --> 37:55.030
Guys, if you'll
just let me--

37:55.050 --> 37:58.710
when we got there, the police were
arresting almost all of those kids,

37:58.740 --> 38:01.160
and 2 of them were taken
away in an ambulance.

38:01.180 --> 38:02.410
I left before they got there.

38:02.440 --> 38:05.220
You weren't supposed to
be there in the first place.

38:05.230 --> 38:08.550
Yeah, at least he's still alive, and I
would be, too, if it weren't for my parents.

38:08.560 --> 38:10.150
- I told you,
ne-- - wait.

38:10.160 --> 38:11.590
Angie's here.

38:11.620 --> 38:13.850
You know what? I have had it with her.

38:13.860 --> 38:15.880
Actually, I think you
may wanna hear this.

38:15.890 --> 38:19.250
Angie, what did you mean about
being dead because of your parents?

38:19.260 --> 38:22.780
I wasn't walking back home
the night I was killed.

38:22.790 --> 38:27.450
I was walking back to the
party to be with my friends.

38:27.470 --> 38:29.090
It's the only place I felt safe.

38:29.100 --> 38:30.850
You were walking back to the party.

38:30.870 --> 38:37.570
Yes, because by the time I'd
gotten home, I was 5 minutes late,

38:37.600 --> 38:42.760
5 stinking minutes late, and my
dad locked me out of the house.

38:42.800 --> 38:48.920
So I started walking back to the
party, and I was crying so hard...

38:49.980 --> 38:52.170
I didn't even hear that car.

38:52.190 --> 38:54.440
What is it? What's going on?

38:54.780 --> 38:57.350
She says her parents locked
her out of the house that night,

38:57.380 --> 38:59.330
Because she missed her
curfew by 5 minutes.

38:59.370 --> 39:00.980
They were that strict.

39:01.010 --> 39:02.970
That's hoible.

39:02.990 --> 39:05.700
I would never do that to Ned.

39:05.720 --> 39:10.680
She says you already have, locked
him out, because you're lying to him.

39:10.690 --> 39:14.300
And she wants to know how's he ever gonna learn from
your mistakes if you're not being honest with him?

39:14.310 --> 39:17.640
That's
not--

39:19.560 --> 39:23.070
ok.You're right.

39:23.080 --> 39:30.190
But you know, what happened to
you, I learned such a huge lesson.

39:30.890 --> 39:35.270
What I mean is a lot of
this is because of you.

39:36.060 --> 39:39.980
When Jody called me that morning
to tell me that you were dead,

39:40.830 --> 39:44.710
My whole life was completely changed.

39:45.470 --> 39:48.380
And when I finally stopped crying,

39:48.410 --> 39:54.500
I vowed that I would never let anything
like that happen to somebody I cared about.

39:57.580 --> 40:00.450
So I guess...

40:00.460 --> 40:06.120
I wouldn't be the mom I
am if I hadn't known you.

40:08.130 --> 40:11.390
And I wouldn't have a son like Ned.

40:12.430 --> 40:16.080
If my parents talked to me like that...

40:16.490 --> 40:19.420
It's never too late, even now.

40:19.430 --> 40:21.450
You can talk to them.

40:21.460 --> 40:24.200
That's genius, Einstein.

40:24.210 --> 40:25.450
I'm dead.

40:25.460 --> 40:27.700
That's what I'm here for.

40:27.710 --> 40:30.480
I already called them.

40:45.050 --> 40:48.950
Just so you know, when I got to
that party, I saw how crazy it was,

40:48.960 --> 40:51.370
so I turned around and came home.

40:51.380 --> 40:53.950
I'm proud of you, Ned.

40:54.440 --> 40:57.720
I'm not sure that's what I would
have done when I was your age.

40:59.400 --> 41:01.500
And I'm sorry for the way I acted.

41:01.510 --> 41:06.390
Good. Me, too.

41:07.680 --> 41:10.220
The truth is I'm always
gonna worry about you.

41:10.230 --> 41:13.640
And the drugs and the drinking,
I know they're all around,

41:13.660 --> 41:15.320
And its not that I don't
trust your judgment.

41:15.340 --> 41:19.460
It's just what happens to your judgment
the second you're drunk or getting high.

41:19.490 --> 41:22.730
Mom, I know.

41:23.680 --> 41:26.110
I'm sorry you lost your friend.

41:27.440 --> 41:29.650
Me, too.

41:39.260 --> 41:41.580
Thank you.

41:52.640 --> 41:56.550
I guess theirs nothin' like a road
trip to help you forget your past.

41:57.090 --> 42:00.230
I mean my past, not your
past. I'm sure yours is fine.

42:00.240 --> 42:02.200
No, I need to move forward, too.

42:02.210 --> 42:04.170
That's good to hear.

42:05.770 --> 42:08.670
Hey, uh, look, I know we just got here.

42:09.800 --> 42:13.610
But, um, you wanna go down
to the village? I don't know.

42:13.620 --> 42:16.500
We could go to a restaurant or, um...

42:16.760 --> 42:19.220
Hit a bookstore. The only bookstore.

42:19.230 --> 42:24.450
Uh, or we could just, you know, get a movie
and then have takeout, come back here, and...

42:25.090 --> 42:26.650
We could, uh...

42:26.680 --> 42:30.550
Go to a hardware store a-and
t some spackle and then...

42:30.570 --> 42:32.730
Spackle?

42:32.740 --> 42:36.150
You know, I think I've forgotten how
to do this along with everything else.

42:36.580 --> 42:38.970
Do what?

42:39.370 --> 42:41.710
Ask somebody out.

42:44.760 --> 42:47.870
- Is that what you're doing?
- Yeah.

42:48.340 --> 42:50.320
Sam!

42:56.640 --> 42:59.480
I got your message, and--and
then I spoke to Cheryl.

42:59.490 --> 43:01.890
I'm so sorry.

43:06.140 --> 43:09.380
Oh, my god. It's true. You
don't know who I am, do you?

43:09.860 --> 43:12.400
I'm sorry.

43:15.160 --> 43:17.690
You must be Nicole.

43:20.310 --> 43:22.870
Nikki. It's Nikki.

